---
// @ts-nocheck
// Import your base layout (handles nav, footer, fonts, meta tags)
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import GradientDivider from "../components/GradientDivider.astro";

// Page metadata - customize these!
const pageTitle = "Discord - Lystaria";
const pageDescription = "Join our diverse community on Discord";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <!-- Main Discord Page Container -->
  <div class="discord-page">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Discord ✦ Lystaria</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        An intentional space for growth, creativity, and shared meaning.
      </p>
    </section>

    <GradientDivider />

    <!-- INFO ABOUT THE SERVER -->
    <section class="info-card">
      <p class="description">
        <strong
          >Lystaria is not just a support server--its a shared ecosystem.</strong
        > It brings together bot support, reading circles, reflective and wellness-focused
        practices, developer conversations, and social spaces for people who dont
        fit neatly into one box. Built on curiosity, creativity, and mutual respect,
        Lystaria is designed to grow with the people who inhabit it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <GradientDivider />

    <!-- HIGHLIGHTS CARD -->
    <section class="highlights">
      <div class="highlights-card">
        <ul class="highlights-list">
          <li>Bot support and thoughtful tool-building</li>
          <li>Reading circles and shared literary exploration</li>
          <li>Wellness-focused reflection and journaling spaces</li>
          <li>Developer conversations and learning together</li>
          <li>Calm, respectful social spaces for connection</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <GradientDivider />

    <!-- MISSION DETAILS -->
    <section class="mission-details">
      <details>
        <summary>What is Lystaria, really?</summary>
        <p>
          Lystaria is more than a collection of Discord bots—it’s an evolving
          ecosystem of tools designed to support personal growth,
          self-awareness, and creative exploration. It exists to accompany you
          as you build a life that feels intentional, grounded, and entirely
          your own, rather than something shaped by pressure, noise, or
          expectation.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every system within Lystaria is created by a single developer with a
          clear vision: to design tools that help you externalize your thoughts,
          maintain meaningful habits, organize your responsibilities, and stay
          connected to what actually matters to you. Whether that’s tracking
          your progress, reflecting on your emotions, or simply remembering the
          small things that tend to slip through the cracks, each feature is
          built to quietly support you in the background of your life.
        </p>
        <p>
          Learning and reflection are also core pillars of this space. Lystaria
          encourages growth through literary and thoughtful mediums—books,
          journaling, shared reading experiences, and written expression—because
          sometimes the most powerful changes come not from doing more, but from
          understanding more.
        </p>
        <p>
          Privacy and comfort are at the center of the experience. Many features
          are designed to live quietly within your Discord DMs, giving you a
          space that feels personal, contained, and fully yours—free from
          outside pressure or visibility. It’s a place where you can think,
          process, and grow at your own pace without feeling watched or judged.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the same time, Lystaria extends outward into community. It provides
          server owners with tools that help shape spaces
          intentionally—balancing safety, flexibility, and structure. The goal
          isn’t rigid control, but empowered design: giving you the ability to
          create an environment that reflects your values, supports your
          members, and evolves alongside your community.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is why Lystaria is built as two distinct yet complementary
          bots—each serving a different role, but working together to form a
          cohesive system. One focuses on personal growth and inner experience,
          while the other supports structure, moderation, and the external
          environment those experiences live within.
        </p>
        <p>
          Together, they create something more than functionality—they create
          alignment between your internal world and the spaces you build around
          you.
        </p>
        <p>
          Keep scrolling to explore both systems and discover how they can
          support you, your community, and the world you’re building.
        </p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <GradientDivider />

    <!-- ELYSIUM INTRODUCTION -->
    <section class="info-card">
      <p class="description">
        Elysium is a companion bot designed for personal growth, reflection, and
        mindful living—helping you track moods, build habits, journal your
        thoughts, and stay connected to what matters most. It lives quietly
        within your space, offering structure, insight, and support in a way
        that feels natural, private, and entirely your own.
      </p>

      <img src="/images/elysium.svg" alt="Elysium Bot" class="bot-image" />

      <details>
        <summary>Read More About Elysium Bot</summary>
        <p>
          Elysium is a versatile, deeply personal bot built from a simple
          frustration: nothing quite fit. In 2025, after constantly searching
          for tools that could support my own routines, reflections, and
          interests without feeling clunky or disconnected, I decided to build
          something that actually did. The name “Elysium” is inspired by the
          Elysian Fields—a place of peace, rest, and fulfillment—and that energy
          sits at the core of everything this bot is meant to be: calm,
          supportive, and quietly powerful.
          <br /><br />
          At its heart, Elysium is designed to live with you, not around you. Most
          features can be used privately within your Discord DMs, giving you a space
          to think, track, and grow without distraction. It’s entirely slash-command
          driven for now, with a full dashboard already in development to expand and
          refine the experience even further.
          <br /><br />
          Journaling was one of the first problems I needed to solve, so it became
          a foundational feature. You can create, view, and manage your entries directly
          from your DMs, allowing you to capture thoughts as they happen without needing
          a separate app or system. It’s simple, accessible, and always within reach—designed
          to remove friction from the act of reflection.
          <br /><br />
          Reminders followed closely behind. Elysium supports flexible recurring reminders—daily,
          weekly, and monthly—so you can stay aligned with your routines without constantly
          rethinking them. Whether it’s something small or something essential, the
          goal is consistency without overwhelm.
          <br /><br />
          Habits are the structure beneath everything we build in our lives, so this
          feature was non-negotiable. With a few guided interactions, you can set
          up habits directly through buttons and modals, making the process feel intuitive
          instead of technical. It’s about reinforcing the patterns that actually
          move you forward.
          <br /><br />
          Reading is another core pillar of Elysium. You can host or join buddy reads,
          pair with others through announcements, and even communicate with your reading
          partner through DM-based commands. Reading sprints allow you to track your
          progress in real time—logging your pages at the start and end, receiving
          automated reminders, and even participating in leaderboards for those who
          enjoy a bit of competition. There’s also a fully customizable recommendation
          system, allowing you to discover new books based on your preferred genres
          and language whenever you want.
          <br /><br />
          Altogether, Elysium is designed to support growth in a way that feels natural,
          not forced—giving you tools for reflection, structure, and learning without
          overwhelming your space. It’s not just about doing more, but about doing
          what matters, consistently and with intention.
        </p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <!-- PANDORYX INTRODUCTION -->
    <section class="info-card">
      <p class="description">
        Pandoryx is a powerful moderation and server management bot built to
        help you shape your community with clarity, control, and intention. From
        automation and protection to customizable systems, it gives you the
        tools to create a space that runs smoothly while still feeling uniquely
        yours.
      </p>

      <img src="/images/pandoryx.svg" alt="Pandoryx Bot" class="bot-image" />

      <details>
        <summary>Read More About Pandoryx Bot</summary>
        <p>
          Pandoryx was built to solve a different kind of problem—the external
          structure of a space. While many moderation bots focus purely on
          control or punishment, Pandoryx is designed around clarity,
          customization, and intentional server design. It gives you the ability
          to shape your environment in a way that feels structured without
          becoming restrictive.
          <br /><br />
          At its core, Pandoryx is about making server management feel seamless. Instead
          of juggling multiple tools or complicated setups, it brings everything into
          one cohesive system that works with you. From the moment you begin configuring
          your server, the goal is to reduce friction and give you control without
          overwhelming you.
          <br /><br />
          Roles and access are one of the most important parts of any community, and
          Pandoryx provides multiple ways to handle them. You can create reaction
          roles for quick interaction, or use fully menu-based role systems that feel
          more guided and polished for your members. This allows you to design onboarding
          experiences that are clear, flexible, and easy to navigate.
          <br /><br />
          Custom embeds are another major feature. With rich embed tools, you can
          create structured, visually consistent messages for announcements, information
          panels, or interactive systems. Instead of relying on plain text, you can
          present your server in a way that feels intentional and well-designed.
          <br /><br />
          Behind the scenes, Pandoryx includes a growing set of server configuration
          settings that let you define how your community operates. From moderation
          tools to automated systems, everything is built to help maintain a safe,
          stable environment while still giving you the flexibility to adapt as your
          server evolves.
          <br /><br />
          Altogether, Pandoryx isn’t just about moderation—it’s about building a space
          that runs smoothly, reflects your values, and supports the people inside
          it. It gives you the structure you need, without taking away the freedom
          to create something that feels entirely your own.
        </p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <GradientDivider />

    <!-- Invite Button Section -->
    <section class="invite-section">
      <h2>Ready to Join?</h2>
      <p class="invite-description">
        Click the button below to get your invite link and become part of our
        community.
      </p>

      <!-- Discord Invite Button -->
      <a
        href="https://discord.gg/aggfkxkBjW"
        class="discord-button"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        <svg
          class="discord-icon"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          viewBox="0 0 127.14 96.36"
          fill="currentColor"
        >
          <path
            d="M107.7,8.07A105.15,105.15,0,0,0,81.47,0a72.06,72.06,0,0,0-3.36,6.83A97.68,97.68,0,0,0,49,6.83,72.37,72.37,0,0,0,45.64,0,105.89,105.89,0,0,0,19.39,8.09C2.79,32.65-1.71,56.6.54,80.21h0A105.73,105.73,0,0,0,32.71,96.36,77.7,77.7,0,0,0,39.6,85.25a68.42,68.42,0,0,1-10.85-5.18c.91-.66,1.8-1.34,2.66-2a75.57,75.57,0,0,0,64.32,0c.87.71,1.76,1.39,2.66,2a68.68,68.68,0,0,1-10.87,5.19,77,77,0,0,0,6.89,11.1A105.25,105.25,0,0,0,126.6,80.22h0C129.24,52.84,122.09,29.11,107.7,8.07ZM42.45,65.69C36.18,65.69,31,60,31,53s5-12.74,11.43-12.74S54,46,53.89,53,48.84,65.69,42.45,65.69Zm42.24,0C78.41,65.69,73.25,60,73.25,53s5-12.74,11.44-12.74S96.23,46,96.12,53,91.08,65.69,84.69,65.69Z"
          ></path>
        </svg>
        Join Discord Server
      </a>
    </section>
    <!-- Additional helpful info -->
    <p class="invite-info">
      By joining, you agree to follow our community guidelines and Discord's
      Terms of Service.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ====================================
     HERO SECTION
     ==================================== */
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Subtitle under the main heading */
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.909); /* Slightly dimmed white */
    max-width: 700px; /* Keep lines readable */
    margin: 0 auto; /* Center it */
  }

  /* ====================================
      INFO SECTION
     ==================================== */
  .info-card {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .description {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 0.45rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 2px dotted transparent;
    border-image: var(--gradient-accent) 1;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  /* ====================================
     BOT IMAGE SECTION
    ==================================== */
  .bot-image {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 260px;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    object-fit: contain;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  /* ====================================
   HIGHLIGHTS CARD
   ==================================== */
  .highlights {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  /* Card container */
  .highlights-card {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    /* Matches your overall dark/glass vibe */
    background: var(--overlay-gradient-accent);
    /* Subtle depth */
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06) inset,
      0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
  }

  /* List */
  .highlights-list {
    list-style: disc;
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;

    display: grid;
    gap: 0.65rem;

    text-align: left;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Make bullets subtle and on-brand without hardcoding colors */
  .highlights-list li::marker {
    color: currentColor;
    opacity: 0.65;
  }

  /* ====================================
     INVITE BUTTON SECTION
     ==================================== */
  .invite-section {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .invite-description {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* ====================================
     DISCORD INVITE BUTTON
     ==================================== */
  .discord-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-family: "Berkshire Swash", serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--overlay-gradient-accent);
    border: none;
    color: #ffffff;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    text-decoration: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  /* Button hover effect */
  .discord-button:hover {
    background: var(--gradient-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow:
      0 6px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4),
      0 0 30px rgba(90, 200, 250, 0.3);
  }

  /* Button active/pressed state */
  .discord-button:active {
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  /* Discord icon styling */
  .discord-icon {
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    flex-shrink: 0; /* Prevents icon from squishing */
  }

  /* Info text below button */
  .invite-info {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); /* Very dim text */
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ====================================
     RESPONSIVE DESIGN (Mobile)
     ==================================== */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    /* Smaller subtitle */
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    /* Adjust button padding on mobile */
    .discord-button {
      padding: 0.9rem 1.5rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .highlights-card {
      padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    }

    .highlights-list {
      padding-left: 1.1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
